    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "```ruby\r\nclient = Neovim.attach_unix('nvim.sock')\r\nclient.subscribe('event')\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn nvim I do `:call rpcnotify(0, 'event')`\r\n\r\nHow do I know that the event has happened?\r\n\r\nI wish the API was something like `client.subscribe('event', |args| print(args))`.\r\n\r\nI see no trace of anything similar to [`next_message()`](https://pynvim.readthedocs.io/en/latest/api/nvim.html#pynvim.api.Nvim.next_message) or [`run_loop(request_cb = None, notification_cb = lambda event, args: print(args))`](https://pynvim.readthedocs.io/en/latest/api/nvim.html#pynvim.api.Nvim.run_loop) in the public API docs.\r\n\r\nPublic method [from_event_loop](https://rubydoc.info/github/neovim/neovim-ruby/Neovim%2FClient.from_event_loop) takes private type [`EventLoop`](https://rubydoc.info/github/neovim/neovim-ruby/Neovim/EventLoop) as argument, which is constructed in the [attach](https://github.com/neovim/neovim-ruby/blob/25560e46e2d0027c8c6e4b000b16e9376d8253c5/lib/neovim.rb#L74), but I see nothing like public API for `EventLoop::read`.",
    "closed_at": "2024-02-22T21:47:02Z",
